<br>
Well to add insult to injury, it appears on their test server verant is attempting to quiet us up with summoned trinkets. Sorry verant, its just not going to be that easy. <br>
<br>
Below i feel are some reasonable upgrades our class should be asking for, to both bring us to somewhere as useful as we were before, and to make good on the claim that &quot;mages are respectible damage dealers&quot;.<br>
<br>
============================================<br>
-1.1 <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>     PET CHANGES</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:<br>
-1.2 <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>OFFENSE</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> (mage only change): <br>
*GV pets now quad for 80 with the exception of fire who will quad for 60, epic quads for 90.<br>
*All mage pets will proc 15% more than currently.<br>
*Fire pet will cast level 39 wizard spells. <br>
*Rogue pet will backstab for 300 max. <br>
<br>
-1.3 <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u> DEFENSE</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> (mage only change): <br>
*Mage pet mitigational abilities and hp will all be increased 20%.<br>
*L60 mage pet heal will now be a common drop.<br>
*L65 upgrade to that heal is planned.<br>
<br>
-1.4 <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>RAID PETS</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> (mage only change):<br>
*New series of dropped and quested bane pets. they are completely imune to ae damage, and have only 500 hp with very high damage output.<br>
<br>
-1.5 <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>GENERAL PET FIXES</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> (will apply to all pet casters):<br>
*Pets now take 75% less ae damage than a pc will.<br>
*Pets now will be included in group ae healing and buffing spells.<br>
*Z-axis pathing related bug with pets will be addressed and a fix is planned.<br>
*Remove the fragment of old anti-train code from when pets were classified as npc and allow more than 4 of them to engage mobs in outdoor zones.<br>
*Pets now use the casting effectiveness level of their master (i.e. pet spells will now be resisted as if you were casting them)<br>
*New switch: /pet bash. will toggle pet bashing on and off (desirable if raiding to position mobs).<br>
*New switch: /pet cast. will toggle pet casting on and off (desirable if raiding magic imune mobs).<br>
*Pet hold is now a standard primary pet caster skill at L61.<br>
<br>
============================================<br>
-2.1 <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>     SPELL CHANGES</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:<br>
<br>
-2.2 <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>OFFENSE</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->:<br>
*<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u> Shock of Steel</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> change; 900/275 (3.27 ratio), 5.5 cast 2.5 refresh delay (112 dps alone, 163 dps with another nuke).<br>
*<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u> Shock of Steel #2</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> at level 60 (drop a little more common than the wizards elernicks); 1200/333 (3.6 ratio), 6.5 cast 2.5 refresh delay (133 dps alone, 185 dps with another nuke).<br>
*<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u> Shock of Fiery Blades</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> change; 1300/361 (3.6 ratio), 6.5 cast 2.5 refresh delay (144 dps alone, 200 dps with another nuke).<br>
*Make <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u> maelstrom of electricity</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> considerably less resistable<br>
*<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u> Fire lure</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> at L57, magic, 600/300 (2 ratio), 5 cast 2.5 refresh delay (80 dps alone, 120 dps with another nuke), -260 resist.<br>
*<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u> Magic lure</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> at 60, fire, 620/300 (2.06), 5 cast 2.5 refresh delay (80 dps alone, 120 dps with another nuke), -300 resist.<br>
*<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u> Scintillation #2</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> at 58. 700/420 same cast and recast delay (to compensate for our loss of a ae group role).<br>
<br>
*So as to keep things more balanced against wizards, lower the mana cost of sunstrike to 420, lower the cost of elernics to 484, and lower the cost of ice spear to 285. The point of these changes is to distinctly define mages as second best nuker, while only slightly closing in on the gap with wizards. Currently druid spells were just too good relative to wizzies to make this happen. So, to avoid nerfing druids, i had to upgrade both mages and wizards in varying degrees while excluding druids in this theoretical change.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>     *Be sure to maintain the same margin of superiority between druid, mage, and wizard nukes as i present here, in pop.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Be sure to fix those god awful new rains.<br>
<br>
